Older than §chumans§r, yet younger than §5dragonkin§r, §6dwarves§r take the middle-child place in the hierarchy of the prime races. 

During the early ages, a great catastrophe befell the dwarves in their endless delve, as they reached §5the §5void§r and fell prey to its horrors. The experience led all dwarves to abolish the practice of arcane magic, which they believed to be linked to the monstrosities that were loosed that day, and that it empowers them. 

The advent of humans was thought to be beneficial to their kind; a potential ally in the war against the arcane, and the dragonkin that wielded it. But it soon became clear that humans had very little concern for such matters, and their §cgreat machines§r have become anathematic blight on the §3Overworld§r, polluting its skies, tarnishing and destroying much of the once-plentiful §9Aetherium§r, scarring the ground and making it poisonous, the elements themselves reeling from the abuse. 

Dwarves see draconic spellcasting as evil, but admire their §6tinkering§r, seeing it as a masterful manipulation of the most primal element, which dwarves themselves have not yet come to understand. Of humans, they delight in the wonders of §6mechanical law§r but abhor their overambitious and "wasteful" use of the same, seeing uncontrolled industrialization for the damage it wreaks on the world around it.

§4Gnomes§r are cursed §chumans§r, their typical knowledge and skill for engineering and reliable mechanics all but utterly extinguished. In its place, fanatical creativity is found, as if desperate to reinvent their lost mastery which their forebears jealously guard. 

Cast out of their urban homes, gnomes were considered to be tainted by the arcane and the horrors of the deep (and indeed, they may well be). Lost and alone on the surface, the gnomes were taken in by §6dwarves§r who found their penchant for invention to be invaluable, profiting from gnomish innovation which rocketed them forward whole ages in advancements. 

The gnomes, for their part, benefit from dwarven protection and muscle, allowing their visions to come to light from the safety of a willing and stalwart guardianship. Gnomes are the creators of the §4GNACK§r Skill.

§5Dragonkin§r are the oldest of the races, and practice the oldest discipline form: §5magic§r. 

Magic has been present since the dawn of time and is built on §5principles§r that have weathered the eons agelessly. In theory, the §5forces§r of magic are the ultimate in conservation. No more magic exists today than did at the dawn of time, and no less. Thus it is slow to develop, difficult to innovate and not as adaptable in application as the other two disciplines of §ctechnological law§r and §6magitechnical elements§r. 

Dragonkin believe themselves to have direct lineage from their §5feral dragon§r cousins and that they are thus "refined" forms of the same thing, though they possess no breath weapons and cannot fly of their own volition. 

They see §chumans§r as young upstarts whose §chubris§r will punish them for trying to equal dragons who are their natural superiors. They see §7§6dwarves§r as admirable for their skills, but loathsome for dwarven §6greed§r which rivals that of their own. Likewise they consider the art of dwarven element manipulation to be inferior to that of the §5arcane arts§r.

The menu you're clicking through right now comes from §eBetter Questing§r. You can open this menu by pressing the tilde §9~§r key, or by opening the §9Quest Book§r that you'll receive for completing this quest. 

Quests are grouped by themes in different Questlines. They can be single quests, appear in chains, or have more complex (or even hidden) rules for unlocking and completing them. 

Some complete automatically when you finish it's last goal and some require input for completion and they'll always have some kind of reward. You'll get a notification each time you complete and unlock a quest. 

Note this quest also has more than 1 reward. Take a moment to use the arrow buttons in the frame below to view all rewards and check the box on the right when you're done.

§dPeches§r are cursed §6dwarves§r; mutated, stunted, and §davarice§r-consumed. 

They are unfriendly to anyone unless placated with §dtreasures§r, and their penchant for hoarding has brought them under the gaze of the dragonkin. Their continual draw to §5dragonkin§r, dragons, and their lairs for their riches has bred a unique dynamic: peches seek treasure and bring it back to their draconic masters, in exchange they share in a wealth they could not possibly acquire by themselves. 

Peches are remarkable masters of §darcane arts§r, for reasons not yet known, and dragonkin pay them handsomely for their work. Pech are the creators of the §dNURVE§r Skill.
No Description

Welcome to§2§2§6 MMO - Let's Go!§f We'll get right to it: This pack is different from anything you've ever seen. We§r §l§rreally, §oreally, §lreally §rrecommend you play through this tutorial. It only takes a few minutes and you'll get some rewards for playing along.

§cYou should not just close this window then run off and see what happens - §nYou'll die and it will suck.§r 

Hit the §lClaim§l§r button below to complete this quest, then hit the §lBack§r button to be returned to the tutorial questline menu. From there, you can continue onto the next quest.

1:10.description:8: Set game difficulty to Passive. But, just for a little while to let you finish these quests.

betterquesting:10.desc:8:
If you've never played §aMMO - Let's Go §fbefore, §fbe aware that it comes with some unique and powerful challenges. This questline will serve to ease you into the experience. Some quests, like this one, have more text than others. You can use the scroll bar on the right or your mousewheel to see the rest of the quest text. 

When you completed the previous quest, we changed the game difficulty to peaceful so you can finish reading this questline without worrying about being mauled by a §9Zombie§r. 

Sorry to trick you! Don't worry, we'll set it back to normal at the very end, and you'll get a warning when it comes. If you're the creator or host of your world you can change your gamemode at any time by §rusing the §o/difficulty§r command. 

When you're ready to move on, click the §lCheckbox §ron the right followed by §lDetect/Submit§r and then §lClaim§r the reward and unlock the next quest.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Difficulty and Where am I Going? (WAIG)
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
In §a§aMMO - Let's Go §r§reach overworld biome has a "difficulty" level. Each time you transition from one biome to another, a message will appear on the screen letting you know the name of the biome and its difficulty level. This message is powered by the mod §e§eWhere am I going? (WAIG). §r§rYou'll find different mobs appearing in different biomes, and the higher the diffiiculty, the more challenging the mobs. 

The ore you find will also increase in value as difficulty increases. Dungeons and ruins increase in complexity, as does the treasure you will find within.

You should start in a level 1 biome and work your way up as you need greater ores and treasures. If you're struggling in a high level biome, consider relocating to a lower level one until you're ready to take on the challenge. §o§oDon't worry about finding one, §r§rwe'll get you set up toward the end of this tutorial.

Biomes now spawn together in climate bands. That means that when traveling longitudinally (East and West) you will find biomes that have similar temperature and traveling lattitudinally (North or South) you will find the temperature rises and falls as if traveling around a globe. Biomes with extreme temperature differences are also much less likely to spawn side-by-side.

To help you navigate this new world, we've included §l§l§l§eAntique Atlas§r. This book automatically maps terrain as you travel and lets you set waypoints to help you remember points of interest. By placing the §9Antique Atlas§r in your toolbar, you can also view the atlas as a minimap. To activate, you must right click after creating it. §o

Have one on the house!

Keep an eye on your experience! Collecting and managing experience is a key component of §aMMO - Let's Go!§r

Take a moment to close your §9Quest Book§r, open your inventory, and click on the §9Skills§r tab on the left. 

In this new menu, you will see a variety of skill trees, created using §eReskillable§r. These §9Skills§r represent the core disciplines of §aMMO - Let's Go§r. BAWLS, GRAYCE, and SKILLZ are the primary disciplines through which players experience content. NURVE, POYSE, and GNACK represent specialized secondary disciplines focused on connecting the primary disciplines.

Each §9Skill§r tree contains a number of §9Traits§r; 20 for primary trees, and 10 for secondary trees. §9Traits§r allow you to learn how to make and use related items. To gain a §9Trait§r, experience must be invested in the §9Skill§r to earn skill points. Points in a §9Skill§r may be spent on §9Traits§r for that tree. Invested experience permanently increases your §9Skill§r level, which likewise increases the amount of experience needed to advance to the next level. Many §9Traits§r have a required minimum level in the §9Skill§r to be selected. So invest early and often!

To see all items that a particular §9Trait§r teaches, simply type the §9Trait's§r name in the search bar for §eJEI§r!

Accidents happen. §c§c§c§cCreepers§r§r§r§r also happen. 

Death is a normal part of playing this pack. When you die, you'll drop your experience and all your items except your armor, toolbar, main and off-hands, and your §9§9§9§9Backpack§r§r§r§r. We highly recommend keeping your most important items in your §9§9§9§9Backpack§r§r§r§r. Lost items and a portion of your experience will be stored in a §9Gravestone§r with your name on it at the site of your death. You also lose 10% equipment durability but it will never reduce below a durability of 1 (dying will never break your equipment). 

When you respawn, you'll have reduced health, reduced hunger, and some minor debuffs, but only for a moment and you can eat to get rid of the effect right away. You can find §9Grave Scrolls§r that will teleport you back to your last death location and we recommend you carry a few of those around in your backpack at all times. 

We do not recommend messing around with the game rule for dropping items on death. That might complicate things.

§eWearble Backpacks§r increases your carrying capacity by serving as a separate inventory that rides around on your back. 

You can place them on the ground, interact with them like a chest, and dye them to your favorite color. When in your inventory, you can place the §9Backpack§r like a normal block. To equip, place it on the ground then hold §l§r§oshift + left click§r with an open hand until it breaks. To unequip, §oshift + right click§r on the ground with an open hand. You may access an equipped §9Backpack's§r inventory by pressing §o§9§r§r§o§9§oI§r. 

Most importantly, items you place in your §9Backpack§r will not be lost on death and you will respawn with it on your body. Use them to protect your most precious items!

You might have noticed by now that §aMMO - Let's Go§r will require you to travel a lot. 

§eWaystones §rgives you a method of fast travel to assist with exploration.

This quest will give you a §9Warp Stone§r which can be used to teleport you to any §9Waystone§r you've previously located. §9Waystones§r can be found in villages and will be uniquely named for the village itself and can be used to teleport between each other. The §9Warpstone§r has a cooldown, however, so to supplement the cooldown you can carry §9Return Scrolls§r, §9Bound Scrolls§r, and §9Warp Scrolls§r. Locate them in §eJEI§r to learn more about how they each work.

This one is optional, but we recommend the following tweaks to improve your experience. Finishing this quest will turn off the spreading of fire, turn off showing of death messages, and reduce the randomtick speed from 3 to 2. 

We recommend these changes because fire will burn the entire world down, showing of death messages can get really spammy with some of the mobs that are in this pack, and reducing the randomtick speed showed a modest performance improvement at the cost of plants growing unnoticeably slower. Is this all personal preference? Sure.

If you don't like the results, you can always modify them later using the following commands:

/gamerule doFireTick
/gamerule showDeathMessages
/gamerule randomTickSpeed

Now, not only §cCreepers§r can come ruin your house. There are many mobs that can do great and terrible things to your home, so we'll now set the doMobGriefing gamerule to false. This gamerule stops mobs from being able to destroy the blocks around them.

If you like the extra challenge and are the creator or host of your world, you can change this back any time with the command below:

/gamerule doMobGriefing

Remember §9Emeralds§r? §oYeah, we don't like carrying them around, either§r. 

We like cold, hard cash, and now, so do villagers. Nearly all villagers have been given entirely new trade tables and accept §9Copper Coins§r and §9Silver Coins§r as payment and only sell items in exchange for currency (not the other way around). There are more than 700 items for sale across all villagers, so you should find a lot of nice and useful surprises as you trade with them. All mobs have a chance of dropping coins and more challenging mobs drop more coins than less challenging ones.

Coins trade up in increments of 8. That is to say that 8 §9Copper Coins§r equal 1 §9Silver coin§r, 8 §9Silver Coins§r equal 1 §9Gold coin§r, and so on. You can trade up or trade down coins in your inventory with the commands below:

/coins stack
/coins unstack

If you're familiar with the mods in §aMMO - Let's Go§r, you'll quickly find that there have been a lot of changes to recipes. We aimed to make the mods feel more like they belonged together, rather than just shoving them together §okitchen-sink-style§r. But, that means we've changed things up quite a bit. 

§eJust Enough Items (JEI)§r is your best friend for crafting items and learning what items can be used for. Take a moment to open your inventory and look to the right - that's the §eJEI§r interface. There's a search bar on the bottom you can use to filter and find what you're looking for. If you want to know how to craft an item, mouse over it and press the §9R§r key. If you want to know what recipes an item is used in, mouse over and press the §9U§r key. 

§eJEI§r is capable of much more than that, so go check it out!

With each discipline is an accompanying §9Faction§r. §9Factions§r represent the typical users of a discipline and are divided along the lines of some typical fantasy species. 

Each §9Faction§r has a unique style or character from the others, a leading fantasy specie, and other §9Factions§r it either clashes or allies with. We will explore each primary §9Faction§r in its own introduction. 

Players may choose to associate with any §9Factions§r corresponding to a §9Skill§r. Each §9Faction§r has a set of preferred biomes, crafting methods, dimensions, armor, weapons, construction materials, and aesthetics. A §9Faction's§r preferences can set the tone for its players, providing a unique look and feel to gameplay.

In the next few quests, you'll get an introduction to each and be allowed to choose 1 to get the first 2 §9Traits§r for free! Choose wisely, as you may only choose one of the §9Factions§r.

betterquesting:10.name:8: BAWLS and the Dwarves of Dawnholdt
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
§o"Nobody does it better!"§r

Living in mighty underground strongholds of ancient carven stone where the music of hammers sound on anvil heads under the roar of furnaces are the §6dwarves§r of §6Dawnholdt§r. 

The masters of the long-lived dwarven tradition of §6magitech§r known as §6BAWLS!§r Priding themselves in the §6quality§r of their work, the dwarves of Dawnholdt§r are an uncompromising lot. They favor hands-on hard work over automated processes and reliance on high-quality §9Dawnstone§r over outright magic or raw ore. Take pride in your work!

Magitech is a loose term for the manipulation of primal elements through pseudo-scientific means of alchemy, metallurgy, and archaic machinery to create §6artifacts§r of power far greater than the two disciplines of technology and magic can produce by themselves. Practitioners of BAWLS§r should feel like §6masters§r of their craft and that what they produce is sought-after and prized.

betterquesting:10.name:8: GRAYCE and the Dragons of the Mystic Accord
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
§o"Behold, the wizard! Beware his powers!"

Unspeakable powers!§r In their resplendent towers loftily gazing over serene green forests and lush jungles, the §5dragonkin§r of the §5Mystic Accord§r are a loose alliance of separate houses banded together under the irrestistible magnet of self-interest. 

Though not all dragonkin agree on every detail, the collected knowledge of the §5arcane arts of §5thaumaturgy§r has become known as §5GRAYCE§r between them. There is no force greater, no cause more noble, and no peoples more worthy of your time. Behold the face of true power!

Magic is arcane, unknowable, and mighty. Practitioners of §5magic§r should feel mysterious, strong, and able to match toe-to-toe with any foe. Both convenience- and combat-oriented, magic lends itself to adventure, discovery, grandeur and treasures.

betterquesting:10.name:8: SKILLZ and the Humans of Stevannia
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
§o"There’s a tool for that."

O' §cStevannia§r, the greatest of lands that ever shall be, and hail the §cSupreme Leader Herobrine§r, its magnificent leader! The §chuman§r citizens of Stevannia are the masters of the art of engineering §cSKILLZ§r. 

Resourceful, inventive, and striving to survive in a hostile world, the people of Stevannia have rapidly advanced in technological prowess to solve their every need with specialized §cequipment and machinery§r. Quality of life comes first!

Tech is new, innovative, exciting, and bold, based on understanding the principles of the physical world and how to bend it with nothing more than your own two hands (and a lot of §csteel§r). Practitioners of §ctechnology§r should feel like nothing is beyond their reach with enough elbow-grease. The experience of day-to-day life and adventuring alike should feel convenient, eased and facilitated by know-how.

It's not safe to go alone. §oIt's also not safe to go naked.§r We'll get you a basic set of §9Leather Armor§r that should see you through the earlier parts of your experience. 

Also note that this (and many other armor sets) have §eSet Bonuses§r. Wearing multiple pieces of the set will grant increasingly powerful bonuses in addition to its normal abilities.

You can wear all of the parts of a given set for the best bonuses, or mix and match parts of different sets for unique combinations.

Suit up!

We've developed §aMMO - Let's Go§r to have a natural progression that follows the biomes, mobs, drops, ore spawns, and traits in a sensical order.  

§aIn MMO - Let's Go§r, ore spawns change from biome to biome, and tier to tier. You can't just hold up in a single biome and find every resource you'll need. By the end of this tutorial, you'll get a feel for how to progress through the content and understand that we want you to explore many biomes in increasing order of difficulty.

For instance, you will not find §9Iron Ore§r in tier 1 biomes. This might sound crazy, but we've also changed many recipes and introduced new ways of doing things that will reduce your demand for §9Iron Ore§r until you're further along. 

Ore also spawns in different shapes and at different heights than you may be used to. You might find ore in veins, sheets, clouds, or dikes that are full of liquid. Ore spawns occur less frequently than you are used to, but they spawn in much, §r§omuch§r larger sizes. §o

§7§oOdds are, if you find a single spawn of an ore type, it will be all the ore you need for quite a while!§r

Arguably, getting you to the right starting biome is the single most important part of §aMMO - Let's Go! §r

With the way Minecraft spawning works, that's a tough feat, so we have to ask you to help us out with this one. To get you to the right biome, we need you to teleport yourself there with a command. 

Use the command §9/biomesop tpbiome <biomename>§r to get you to the biome of your choice. Just replace <biomename> with the fully qualified name of the biome you want. If you hit §9TAB§r while typing the command, it will help you with a list of options.

We recommend choosing tier 1 biome listed under the faction you chose in the previous quest. If you're still unsure, we've got some samples below for each faction. You'll have to type this into chat yourself and run it.

§6Dwarves of Dawholdt - BAWLS§r
/biomesop tpbiome biomesoplenty:highland
/biomesop tpbiome minecraft:mutated_redwood_taiga

§5Dragons of the Mystic Accord - GRAYCE§r
/biomesop tpbiome minecraft:jungle
/biomesop tpbiome biomesoplenty:grove

§cHumans of Stevannia - SKILLZ§r
/biomesop tpbiome biomesoplenty:dead_forest
/biomesop tpbiome minecraft:desert

The command can take a minute to run. Sometimes it doesn't work because the nearest instance of the biome you entered is too far for it to find. You will need to change which biome you want to go to and try again.

When you're settled, finish this quest and use the command §9/sethome §rto make sure you spawn at home the next time you die. 


§n§r§o§8§7Look, we know this isn't perfect, but getting you to the right starting biome is absolutely necessary to set you up for success. Remember in the first quest where we said you'd die a lot and it will suck? We were mostly talking about where to start.

betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Alright, that's it! The tutorial is now over. Thanks for hanging in there. 

We'll go ahead and set the gamemode back to normal difficulty and you can move along. We have so much more to come in future releases, but the core skills we covered in this tutorial should be more than enough to get you started. As always, check out our §9Discord§r and §9Issues Page§r on §9Curseforge§r if you have trouble or want to provide feedback. 

We're always looking for more beta testers, so come talk to us and thank you for playing!

1:10.description:8: Finishing this quest will set the game difficulty back to 2 (normal) and also set your home to make extra sure that you won't be accidentally sent back to the world spawn.

betterquesting:10.desc:8:
The youngest of the prime races, §chumans§r have found themselves in a unique position, their survival in an ancient world filled with hostility has shaped them into a people dependent on their wits, tools, and ability to adapt rapidly using disciplines that build and evolve across generations. 

Every advancement that humans enjoy today is built on the backs and brains of every human that has ever come before, with their machines the brain-children of not just one mind, but a hundred together, one after the other. As such, human §ctechnology§r requires very little inherent power or talent to use, but a great deal of instruction and training, and in many cases, an outright §cuser’s manual§r. 

Humans consider §5draconic magic§r to be incredible but stifling, as it is known to have not evolved since its advent, and thus has already reached its maximum potential. §6Dwarven§r §6metallurgy§r and §6elemental manipulation§r impresses human §cengineers§r, and many believe there is some physical law at work; however most consider it a pseudoscience, unreliable and thus unusable.

§dKobolds§r are cursed §5dragonkin§r, thus hated by their predecessors and thought to be an ill omen, a source of ruin, and the inevitable destruction of dragon kind should their "disease" spread. 

In reality, they aren’t contagious but superstition makes dragonkin inclined to kill kobolds on-sight. Kobolds allied with §chumans§r, offering their expertise in §dmechanical processes§r and §c§delemental energies§r.
